---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — xeto.dev" description="What xeto.dev is and who runs it">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">About xeto.dev</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-ink-soft">
      <p>
        xeto.dev is the package registry for
        <span class="font-medium text-ink">Xeto</span> — a language for
        defining typed data. Every library here is a versioned collection of
        specs: types, slots, and instances that describe real-world data
        models, from Project Haystack's building ontology to your own
        domain's schemas.
      </p>
      <p>
        Xeto grew out of the
        <a href="https://project-haystack.org" class="text-brand hover:underline">Project Haystack</a>
        community's work on semantic data modeling and is developed in the
        open alongside
        <a href="https://haxall.io" class="text-brand hover:underline">Haxall</a>.
        The registry gives that ecosystem what package managers gave code:
        versioned publishing, dependency resolution, and one place to
        discover what already exists.
      </p>
      <p>
        The site and registry are maintained by
        <a href="https://xetobase.com" class="text-brand hover:underline">XetoBase</a>.
        We're in early access — browsing and installing is open to everyone;
        publishing is invite-only while the tooling settles.
      </p>
      <p>
        Questions, ideas, or want to publish?
        <a href="/contact" class="text-brand hover:underline">Get in touch</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
